<b>Pique verde boricua</b> is a <link>
Puerto Rican</link> green hot sauce made of green Caballero hot peppers, green <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../002/13055002.xml">
Cubanelle pepper</link>s, <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../640/341640.xml">
cilantro</link>, <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../066/1872066.xml">
culantro</link>, <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../258/51258.xml">
onion</link>, <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../469/50469.xml">
garlic</link>, <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../478/22478.xml">
olive oil</link>, and <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../456/261456.xml">
lime juice</link>.<ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%221%22])">1</ref><p>

This sauce may be served with meats, fried fish, tostones, viandas [root vegetables], mofongos, rice  and beans.</p>


